claim.claim-text:
A pre-tensioned breakaway fastener assembly for use in attaching a tooling member to an assembly device, the fastener assembly characterized in that:
an upper annular plate (304) having a first through bore (304a);
a lower annular place (210, 306) axially spaced from the upper plate and having a first through bore (210a, 306a) axially aligned with the upper plate first bore, one of the first and the second annular plates having at least one second through bore (304b) radially spaced from the respective first through bore;
a breakaway fastener (114, 214, 302) having a head (116, 214b, 302a), an end opposite the head, an elongate shank (214a, 302b) between the head and the end, and an assembly device threaded engagement portion (214c, 302d) adjacent the end, the fastener shank further having a predetermined fracture portion having a narrowed cross section (114b, 214d, 302c) portion positioned on the shank between the head and the breakaway fastener assembly devic threaded engagement portion, the breakaway fastener axially positioned through the upper and the lower plate first bores;
a compressible spring member (118, 216, 308) positioned between the upper and lower plates radially spaced from the shank; and
at least one compressive fastener (310) radially spaced from the breakaway fastener and axially positioned through the second bore in one of the upper or lower plate and removably engagable through contact with the other of the plates to axially compress the spring member, wherein the breakaway fastener is adapted to be pretensioned on disengagement of the compressive fastener with the other of the plates.

A method of pre-tensioning a breakaway fastener assembly for use in connecting a tooling member to an assembly device, the fastener assembly including a breakaway fastener (114, 214, 302), an upper (304) and a lower annular plate (210, 306) each having a thickness positioned axially apart, a compression fastener (310) independent of the breakaway fastener and a compression spring member (118, 216, 308), the method comprising the steps of:
positioning the spring member between the upper and the lower plates;
axially positioning the compression fastener through a bore in one of the upper or lower annular plates and removeably engaging the compression fastener in the other of the upper or the lower annular plate;
axially compressing the spring member through advancing axial engagement of the compression fastener into at least a portion of the thickness of the other of the upper or the lower annular plate;
axially positioning the breakaway fastener through axially aligned bores in the upper and lower annular plates and in abutting axial engagement with the spring member;
removably and axially engaging the breakaway fastener with the assembly device opposite the abutting engagement with the spring member; and
disengaging the compression fastener from the other of the upper or the lower annular plate thereby pre-tensioning the breakaway fastener through axial expansion of the springf member against the lower plate and the breakaway fastener.
